"Well, certainly that is also a conceivable hypothesis," said Holmes, smiling. "And now, Lord St.
Simon, I think that I have nearly all my data. May I ask whether you were seated at the breakfast-
table so that you could see out of the window?"

"We could see the other side of the road and the Park."

"Quite so. Then I do not think that I need to detain you longer. I shall communicate with you."

"Should you be fortunate enough to solve this problem," said our client, rising.

"I have solved it."